Text: This past week, I have been proactive in contributing my part of the project.

I have learnt how to apply my learnings from the Udemy course, using a PHP framework to connect the database, used code to scrape data without using R Studio, and have been looking at tutorials to understand how I might connect the work I have done with the webserver.
It has been a big stretch for me to take this all on.

Earlier in the week the group discussed ther project and how it was going, to my knowledge the shortcomings i. e.  the connectivity of R-Studio and the web server, UI design and the database design used were unfortunately not working well together.
I felt I had more to contribute so I offered to explore alternative ways of meeting the deliverables, which resulted in me looking into how it might be achieved using methods not yet tried.

I was fortunate to get advice from a friend regarding the Laravel ecosystem which seemingly met our needs and got to coding, collecting the data form the website and building an ERD which I believed would work.
Come Friday, it seems we have found a solution to our problems and have been able to overcome obstacles by combining the different pieces of work which has been done over the last few weeks.
Coming into this week i am hoping to implement the work I have done to scrape the data as an alternative to R studio due to it being difficult to connect to the web server.
This will need to be iterated on throughout the week.

The beginning of the final report have been about organising and planning to which i have been able to identify key discussion points and aspect of my work which I will focus on building a technical report around.
